As a side note: gvfs volume monitor doesn't emit `MountAdded` for _all_ mounts â€“ as far as I can see, it only does so for mountpoints that are meant to be _visible in the GUI_. So there's no `MountAdded` signal if I manually mount something on `/mnt`.

Using UDisks2 directly may be more reliable (and does not require the desktop session). It is available on the system bus as `org.freedesktop.UDisks2`:

